Extreme Alaska Denali National Park
(2007) National Geographic

This National Geographic documentary takes viewers on a scenic tour through Alaska's Denali National Park. Comprising over two million acres of wilderness the park's impressive landscapes are abundant with a diversity of flora and fauna. This should be of no surprise for a place that's home to glaciers grizzlies and North America's tallest peak Mount McKinley.
